article.headline: San Diego 60, San Jose St. 40
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Brandon Johnson and Gyno Pomare scored 13 points apiece to lead San Diego to a 60-40 win over San Jose State on Wednesday. Johnson also led the Toreros (5-5) with seven rebounds, six assists and six steals. DeVonte Thomas paced the Spartans (3-2) with 11 points and eight rebounds. San Diego used a 13-4 run in a six-minute span of the first half to open up a 21-10 lead at the 6:06 mark. The deficit could have been greater, but the Toreros missed 6 of 8 free throws in the span. San Diego, ahead 25-14 at the half, never led by less than nine points the rest of the way.
